# üöÄ feature request

### Relevant Package
<!-- Can you pin-point one or more @angular/* packages the are relevant for this feature request? -->
<!-- ‚úçÔ∏èedit: --> This feature request is for @angular/core


### Description
```
export class BaseComponent {
}

@Component({
  selector: 'derived1',
  template: `<p>Derived Component 1</p>`,
  providers: [{ provide: BaseComponent, useExisting: DerivedComponent1 }]
})
export class DerivedComponent1 extends BaseComponent {
}

@Component({
  selector: 'derived2',
  template: `<p>Derived Component 2</p>`,
  providers: [{ provide: BaseComponent, useExisting: DerivedComponent2}]
})
export class DerivedComponent2 {
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app',
  template: `
  <derived1></derived1>
  <derived2></derived2>
`
})
export class AppComponent implements AfterViewInit {
@ViewChildren(BaseComponent) children: QueryList<BaseComponent>;

  ngAfterViewInit() {
    console.log(this.children);
  }
}
```
In this example I have `DerivedComponent1` which extends `BaseComponent` and `DerivedComponent2` which does not. 
Both get populated in the `children` query list because they each have a provider declaration for `BaseComponent`.

**Issue:** Is there a way I can declare all providers for BaseComponent at once? Something like:
```
const derivedComponents = [ DerivedComponent1, DerivedComponent2 ];
@Component({
  selector: 'app',
  template: `
  <derived1></derived1>
  <derived2></derived2>
`,
 providers: derivedComponents.map(component => ({ provide: BaseComponent, useExisting: component }))
})
export class AppComponent implements AfterViewInit {
@ViewChildren(BaseComponent) children: QueryList<BaseComponent>;

  ngAfterViewInit() {
    console.log(this.children);
  }
}
```

I've tried this but `children` comes back empty.

### Referenced Issues:
https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/8580
https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/18700

Thanks in advance!

# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/animation


### Is this a regression?

No


### Description

Initially there's an array of objects for *ngFor display in HTML, and each object is assigned a boolean property "show" with value false in OnInit( ). And "show" is used to indicate the animation state 'initial' or 'final' that is defined in component.

The animation 'trigger' works fine at the beginning, but after changing the order of the objects in the array (sort or reverse), Angular Animation seems to lose binding to the objects, and the 'trigger' doesn't do anything when trying to trigger the first time, but it works fine on the second time and so on.

Expected behaviour: after changing order of the objects (sort / reverse), the animation should work at the first 'trigger'.

Please check the stackblitz below.


